title: Inmarsat-6 F2 satellite completes three-day trip to SpaceX launch site
summary: Inmarsat’s latest geostationary telecoms satellite has arrived at its Florida launch site after a three-day journey from Airbus’ testing facilities in France.

title: Former NASA Astronauts to Receive Congressional Space Medal of Honor
summary: Vice President Kamala Harris will award former NASA astronauts Douglas Hurley and Robert Behnken the Congressional Space Medal of Honor at 4:15 p.m. EST on Tuesday, Jan. 31. Hurley and Behnken will receive the award for bravery in NASA’s SpaceX Demonstration Mission-2 (Demo-2) to the International Space Station in 2020.

title: NASA to Air Live Coverage of Spacewalk for Power System Upgrades
summary: Two astronauts aboard the International Space Station will conduct a spacewalk Thursday, Feb. 2, to continue the installation of hardware for future power system upgrades. The spacewalk is scheduled to begin at 8:15 a.m. EST and last about six and a half hours.

title: NASA's Perseverance Rover Completes Mars Sample Depot
summary: Ten sample tubes, capturing an amazing variety of Martian geology, have been deposited on Mars’ surface so they could be studied on Earth in the future.

title: SpaceX delays first flight of cross-country Starlink doubleheader to Tuesday
summary: With five Falcon 9 launches and a single Falcon Heavy flight already under its belt so far in 2023, SpaceX is set to end January and begin February by launching two Starlink missions. These launches will now occur just one day apart from separate launch sites.

title: After a failure 4 months ago, the New Shepard spacecraft remains in limbo
summary: Blue Origin has said nothing publicly about the September failure of New Shepard.

title: Asteroid mining startup AstroForge to launch first missions this year
summary: A startup with plans to mine asteroids for metals says it will launch its first two missions this year, including one that will fly by a near Earth asteroid.

title: LeoLabs scans skies with West Australian Space Radar
summary: LeoLabs announced the commissioning Jan. 30 of its West Australian Space Radar to improve tracking of satellites and debris in low-Earth orbit.

title: SpaceX’s first NASA astronauts to receive Space Medal of Honor for Dragon test flight
summary: NASA says that the astronauts responsible for SpaceX’s first crewed Dragon test flight will be awarded the Congressional Space Medal of Honor...

title: SpaceX’s 100-launch target is more realistic than it seems
